        <item>
            <title>Notes From An Are.na Workshop: Channel As Gift</title>
            <link>https://zacharykai.net/notes/agwdec24</link>
            <pubDate>Wed, 26 Jan 2025 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
            <author>hi@zacharykai.net (Zachary Kai)</author>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">https://zacharykai.net/notes/agwdec24</guid>
            <description>In late December 2024, I attended an Are.na Channel As Gift workshop hosted by Laurel Schwulst. Such a fascinating idea! These are my notes from attending.</description>
            <content:encoded>
                <![CDATA[ <h1>Notes From An Are.na Workshop: Channel As Gift (21 Dec 2024)</h1>
                <p id="top">In late December 2024, I attended an Are.na Channel As Gift workshop hosted by Laurel Schwulst. Such a fascinating idea! These are my notes from attending.</p>
                <ul>
                <li>Gifting as a verb is more nourishing than the noun.</li>
                <li>Gift giving is often separated as its own love language, but you could argue that all other love languages involve the giving of a gift.</li>
                <li>Attention and time are the ingredients for a good gift. Being a good gift giver is about listening, appreciating, and considering. You make connections between disparate things and the people you love.</li>
                <li>Living with the intention of generosity is gift giving at its core. Even something as simple as an email can be a gift: putting in effort shows you care.</li>
                <li>A wonderful gift is a Venn diagram of what you and the recipient enjoy. A moment of connection often becomes more important than the material thing.</li>
                <li>Thoughtful digital gifts: a memory capsule of photos, a playlist, a reader of recommended articles or books, summarizing your shared existence, an imaginary museum, reasons why they're loved, and a to-do list of fun activities</li>
                <li>Gifting as an infinite game is a constant back-and-forth, a way of life.</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>Bibliography</strong></p>
                <ul>
                <li><a href="https://laurelschwulst.com/" target="_blank">Laurel Schwulst's Site</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.are.na/laurel-schwulst/channel-as-gift" target="_blank">The Workshop's Are.na Channel</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.are.na/editorial/gifting-guides" target="_blank">The Workshop's Ethos</a></li>
                </ul>
                <p>•--♡--•</p> ]]>
            </content:encoded>
